The article announces various appointments and reappointments to different positions in the United States government. These include Elliott Abrams being appointed as a Member of the United States Advisory Commission on Public Diplomacy for a term expiring in 2024 and being reappointed for a term expiring in 2027. Derek H. Chollet is appointed as Under Secretary of Defense for Policy, Harry Coker, Jr. as National Cyber Director, Jon M. Holladay as Chief Financial Officer of the Department of Agriculture, and J. Todd Inman as a Member of the National Transportation Safety Board. Stephan A. Lang is appointed as U.S. Coordinator for International Communications and Information Policy, and Joann M. Lockard is appointed as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to Burkina Faso. Rion J. Ramirez is appointed as a Member of the Board of Trustees of the Morris K. Udall and Stewart L. Udall Foundation.